{
  "explanation": "The defendant's actions represent a significant breach of fiduciary duty and professional trust inherent in their role as an accountant. While the lack of a prior criminal record and the partial restitution of the $25,000 are mitigating factors that warrant a sentence below the maximum possible range, the deliberate nature of the embezzlement for personal gain necessitates a term of incarceration to serve as a deterrent and to uphold the integrity of financial systems. A term of 9 months balances the severity of the theft with the defendant's rehabilitative efforts and prior clean history.",
  "verdict": 9
}
